label: edible grain
semantic_ground_truth: SEEDS used as a major nutritional source, most often the grain from the POACEAE family.

label: oocysts
semantic_ground_truth: Zygote-containing cysts of sporozoan protozoa. Further development in an oocyst produces small individual infective organisms called SPOROZOITES. Then, depending on the genus, the entire oocyst is called a sporocyst or the oocyst contains multiple sporocysts encapsulating the sporozoites.

label: sporozoites
semantic_ground_truth: The product of meiotic division of zygotes in parasitic protozoa comprising haploid cells. These infective cells invade the host and undergo asexual reproduction producing MEROZOITES (or other forms) and ultimately gametocytes.

label: schizonts
semantic_ground_truth: Multinucleate cells or a stage in the development of sporozoan protozoa. It is exemplified by the life cycle of PLASMODIUM FALCIPARUM in the MALARIA infection cycle.

label: merozoites
semantic_ground_truth: Uninuclear cells or a stage in the life cycle of sporozoan protozoa. Merozoites, released from ruptured multinucleate SCHIZONTS, enter the blood stream and infect the ERYTHROCYTES.

label: trophozoites
semantic_ground_truth: Cells or feeding stage in the life cycle of sporozoan protozoa. In the malarial parasite, the trophozoite develops from the MEROZOITE and then splits into the SCHIZONT. Trophozoites that are left over from cell division can go on to form gametocytes.

label: edible grain
semantic_ground_truth: SEEDS used as a major nutritional source, most often the grain from the POACEAE family.

label: larva
semantic_ground_truth: Wormlike or grublike stage, following the egg in the life cycle of insects, worms, and other metamorphosing animals.

label: life cycle stages
semantic_ground_truth: The continuous sequence of changes undergone by living organisms during the post-embryonic developmental process, such as metamorphosis in insects and amphibians. This includes the developmental stages of apicomplexans such as the malarial parasite, PLASMODIUM FALCIPARUM.

label: nymph
semantic_ground_truth: The immature stage in the life cycle of those orders of insects characterized by gradual metamorphosis, in which the young resemble the imago in general form of body, including compound eyes and external wings; also the 8-legged stage of mites and ticks that follows the first moult.

label: poultry
semantic_ground_truth: Domesticated birds raised for food. It typically includes CHICKENS; TURKEYS, DUCKS; GEESE; and others.

label: pupa
semantic_ground_truth: An inactive stage between the larval and adult stages in the life cycle of INSECTA.

label: radiation chimera
semantic_ground_truth: An organism whose body contains cell populations of different genotypes as a result of the TRANSPLANTATION of donor cells after sufficient ionizing radiation to destroy the mature recipient's cells which would otherwise reject the donor cells.

label: vegetables
semantic_ground_truth: A food group comprised of EDIBLE PLANTS or their parts.

label: crops, agricultural
semantic_ground_truth: Cultivated plants or agricultural produce such as grain, vegetables, or fruit. (From American Heritage Dictionary, 1982)

label: endogenous retroviruses
semantic_ground_truth: Retroviruses that have integrated into the germline (PROVIRUSES) that have lost infectious capability but retained the capability to transpose.
